---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Best Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Mexico Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
  { title: 'Portugal Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Max Coverage', img: 'Up to $8M', cigna: 'Unlimited' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', img: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', img: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', img: 'Limited', cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Maternity', img: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Dental', img: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Deductible Options', img: '7 choices', cigna: '4 choices' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', img: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Deductible Waiver Outside US', img: '50%', cigna: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Travel Intelligence Alerts', img: true, cigna: false },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', img: '$100-150/mo', cigna: '$140-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', img: '$180-250/mo', cigna: '$220-280/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', img: '$200-300/mo', cigna: '$280-360/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', img: '$350-500/mo', cigna: '$450-600/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global vs Cigna Global"
  description="Compare IMG Global and Cigna Global international health insurance. Budget-friendly vs premium: which is right for you?"
  headline="IMG Global vs Cigna Global: Budget vs Premium Compared"
  subheadline="Should you save money with IMG or pay more for Cigna's premium features? Here's how they compare."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global and Cigna Global represent two different approaches to international health insurance. IMG offers solid coverage at budget-friendly prices, while Cigna provides premium service and a larger network at higher cost.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison helps you decide whether to save money with IMG or invest in Cigna's enhanced features.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Trustpilot:</strong> 4.6/5 (19,000+ reviews)</li>
        <li>Budget-friendly pricing</li>
        <li>7 deductible options for flexibility</li>
        <li>50% deductible waived outside US</li>
        <li>30+ years in business</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Network:</strong> 1.5M+ providers</li>
        <li>Unlimited coverage on top plans</li>
        <li>24/7 multilingual customer service</li>
        <li>Strong direct billing network</li>
        <li>User-friendly app and portal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from IMG Global and Cigna Global for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both providers cover the essentials, but there are meaningful differences in coverage limits, flexibility, and included features.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Differences</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Coverage limits:</strong> Cigna offers unlimited coverage on Platinum plans. IMG caps at $8 million (still very high).</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible flexibility:</strong> IMG offers 7 deductible options ($250-$10,000) vs Cigna's 4 options.</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible waiver:</strong> IMG waives 50% of your deductible for care outside the US—a unique money-saving feature.</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Cigna provides more comprehensive mental health coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Travel alerts:</strong> IMG includes Travel Intelligence with location-specific safety alerts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    This is where IMG shines. Their premiums are typically 20-30% lower than Cigna for comparable coverage levels.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices based on Silver/Gold tier plans excluding US coverage. Actual quotes vary based on specific plan, deductible, and location.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Annual Savings with IMG</h3>
  <p>
    For a 35-year-old individual, choosing IMG over Cigna could save $400-600 per year. For a family, savings could reach $1,200-1,800 annually.
  </p>

  <h3>Factors Affecting Price</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Deductible choice:</strong> IMG's high-deductible options ($5,000-$10,000) offer the biggest savings</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage area:</strong> Both charge much more for US coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Payment frequency:</strong> IMG charges 20% more for monthly payments; pay annually to save</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="See real quotes based on your age, location, and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> has a clear advantage with 1.5 million+ providers and strong direct billing arrangements worldwide. You're more likely to find in-network care and avoid paying upfront.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> has a smaller network but still covers major hospitals in most countries. You may need to pay and file for reimbursement more often.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> processes claims in 5-10 business days with an easy-to-use online portal. Direct billing reduces the need to file claims for major procedures.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> has excellent customer reviews (4.6/5), but claims can take longer—sometimes weeks to months for complex cases. Some customers report slow response times during the claims process.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> offers 24/7 multilingual support with a reputation for responsive, helpful service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> provides 24/7 support in 18 languages with in-house medical staff. Their website and quote process are highly rated, though live chat support receives mixed reviews.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Budget is your top priority</li>
        <li>You want maximum deductible flexibility</li>
        <li>You'll mainly get care outside the US</li>
        <li>You're young and healthy</li>
        <li>You can wait for slower claims processing</li>
        <li>You value the 50% deductible waiver abroad</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Direct billing availability is important</li>
        <li>You want a larger provider network</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage is a priority</li>
        <li>You prefer faster claims processing</li>
        <li>You want premium customer service</li>
        <li>You're willing to pay more for convenience</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>For budget-conscious expats,</strong> IMG Global offers excellent value. You get solid coverage at significantly lower prices, plus unique benefits like the 50% deductible waiver and 7 deductible choices. Their 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating (from 19,000+ reviews) shows customers are generally satisfied.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>For expats who prioritize service and convenience,</strong> Cigna Global is worth the premium. Their larger network, faster claims, and stronger direct billing make the insurance experience smoother—especially valuable if you have ongoing health needs.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Our recommendation:</strong> If you're healthy, cost-conscious, and don't mind occasional out-of-pocket payments while waiting for reimbursement, IMG is an excellent choice. If you want the peace of mind that comes with a larger network and faster claims, invest in Cigna.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change frequently. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
